@NODE Index "View all 34 GadTools Instructions."

View all 34 GadTools Instructions.
----------------------------------

If you have with >>>Include "Device+Path/GadTools.Inc"<<< the GadTools linked
at the end of your Mainprogram, can you now use following Instructions:
(Please read in addition to it also @{"Important !!!" LINK Important})
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Screen_Open[ScreenNumber,Value]

With this Instruction opening you an Screen in OS3.x Look. The first Para-
meter is a ScreenNumber from 0-7. With the 2nd Parameter (Value) can you
choose the ScreenModi. Here can you insert an Number from 0-2.

Value 0 = Lores (320 x 256 x 4)
Value 1 = Hires (640 x 256 x 4)
Value 2 = Laced (640 x 512 x 4)

An Screen that you have so opening is now showing in OS3.x Look.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Make_Mask[X1,Y1,X2,Y2,Color1,Color2,Color3]

This Instruction Draws a Mask that is showing in OS3.x Look. This Mask
will now Draws at the Coordinaates X1,Y1,X2,Y2. Color1 is the Color for
the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With Color3
can you choose the MaskColor. Use this Instruction if possible first when
you have defined the '_Screen_Open' and/or '_WinClone' Instruction.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_PushButton[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,"Button-Name"]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a PushButton. This Button with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color
for the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With
Color3 can you choose the ButtonColor and Color4 for the Text in the Button.
Button-Name defined a Name of the Button. You can defined Max. 30 Push-
Buttons. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Del_PushButton[Id]

This Instruction removes the PushButton with Id-Number 'Id' from Memory.
This Button is now deleted. The GFX from this Button will stay in the
Screen. This Instruction ist very important if you will (for example)
opening an second Screen with other Buttons. If you have the Buttons from
first Screen not removed, you can get problems when the Buttons from
first Screen are not deleted. This Buttons can you then also clicking.
It is better if you remove all Buttons from first Screen with the _Del_Push-
Button Instruction. If you will activate a deleted Button, you must defined
this Button again. (See in addition to it '_PushButton')

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_PushButton_Hit

With this Instruction you can checking all defined PushButtons. When a Push-
Button is clicking, get the variable 'Param' the Id-Number from clicked
Button. If you have no Buttons clicked, the variable 'Param' get '0'.
This Instruction must you have in your Mainroutine of your Program.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_CheckBox[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,On/Off]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a CheckBox. This CheckBox with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color
for the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With
Color3 can you choose the ButtonColor and Color4 for the hack in the Button.
On/Off orders the activate of the CheckBox. You can insert a Number from
0-1. With '1' will Drawing an activated CheckBox and with '0' an inactivated.
You can defined Max. 30 CheckBoxes. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number
from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Set_CheckBox_State[Id,On/Off]


Whit this Instruction can you the CheckBox with ID-Number 'Id' activate
or inactivate. With On/Off can you choose a Value from 0-1. That is:
'0' will inactivate the CheckBox (Hack is not Showing) and '1' activate it.
(Hack in the CheckBox is now Showing)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Get_CheckBox_State[Id]

With this Instruction can you get the State from the CheckBox with ID-
Number 'Id'. The variable 'Param' get '1' when the CheckBox is
activate and '0' when the CheckBox is inactivate. If you get '-1'
then is it an Error. That is: The CheckBox was not defined or the ID-
Number 'Id' is about '30'.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Del_CheckBox[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Del_PushButton[Id] here only for CheckBoxes.
(See in addition to it _Del_PushButton.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_CheckBox_Hit

This Instruction is like with _PushButton_Hit here only for CheckBoxes.
(See in addition to it _PushButton_Hit.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_RadioButton[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,On/Off]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a RadioButton. This Button with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. With Color1 can
you choose the ButtonColor. With Color2 choose you the Color for an
activated Button and Color3 for an inactivated Button. On/Off orders the
activate of the Button. You can insert a Number from 0-1. With '1' will
Drawing an activated Button and with '0' an inactivated. You can defined
Max. 30 RadioButtons. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Set_RadioButton_State[Id,On/Off]

This Instruction is like with _Set_CheckBox_State here only for RadioButtons.
(See in addition to it _Set_CheckBox_State.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Get_RadioButton_State[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Get_CheckBox_State here only for RadioButtons.
(See in addition to it _Get_CheckBox_State.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Del_RadioButton[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Del_PushButton here only for RadioButtons.
(See in addition to it _Del_PushButton.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_RadioButton_Hit

This Instruction is like with _PushButton_Hit here only for RadioButtons.
(See in addition to it _PushButton_Hit.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_CycleButton[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,"Text1|Text2|Text3..."]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a CycleButton. This Button with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color
for the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With
Color3 can you choose the ButtonColor and Color4 for the Texts in the Button.
With Text1|Text2|Text3... can you choose the Texts that will showing in
the Button. All Texts must you insert separate with '|'.  You can defined
Max. 30 CycleButtons. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Set_CycleButton_State[Id,TextNumber]

With this Instruction can you change the State from CycleButton with
ID-Number 'Id'. That is: If you have, for example, 3 Texts in CycleButton
with Id-Number '1' defined and you now with _Set_CycleButton_State[1,2]
changes the State, so showings this CycleButton now the 2nd Text.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Get_CycleButton_State[Id]

This Instruction getting the State of a CycleButton. The result is now
in the variable 'Param'. For example, if the 2nd Text is showing, the
variable 'Param' will have the worth '2'. If you get '-1' then is it
an Error. That is: The CycleButton was not defined or the ID-Number 'Id'
is about '30'.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Del_CycleButton[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Del_PushButton here only for CycleButtons.
(See in addition to it _Del_PushButton.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_CycleButton_Hit

This Instruction is like with _PushButton_Hit here only for CycleButtons.
(See in addition to it _PushButton_Hit.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ToggleButton[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,On/Off,"Button-Name"]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a ToggleButton. This Button with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color
for the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With
Color3 can you choose the ButtonColor and Color4 for the Text in the Button.
With On/Off can you choose a number from 0-1. That is: If you insert '1'
the Button will showing activated and with '0' inactivated. Button-Name
defined a Name of the Button. You can defined Max. 30 ToggleButtons.
The 'Id-No.' must so have a number from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Set_ToggleButton_State[Id,On/Off]

This Instruction is like with _Set_CheckBox_State here only for Toggle-
Buttons. (See in addition to it _Set_CheckBox_State.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Get_ToggleButton_State[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Get_CheckBox_State here only for Toggle-
Buttons. (See in addition to it _Get_CheckBox_State.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Del_ToggleButton[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Del_PushButton here only for ToggleButtons.
(See in addition to it _Del_PushButton.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ToggleButton_Hit

This Instruction is like with _PushButton_Hit here only for ToggleButtons.
(See in addition to it _PushButton_Hit.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_StringGadget[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,Color5,GadLen,MaxTexLen]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a StringGadget with ID-Number 'Id'
on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color for the Top & Left Border and
Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With Color3 can you choose the Button-
Color and with Color4 for the Text in the Button. Color5 defined the Cursor-
Color. GadLen is the length from the StringGadget in Characters and MaxTexLen
defined the Maximal Textlength that you can insert in the StringGadget.
You can defined Max. 30 StringGadgets. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number
from 1-30.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Set_StringGadget_State[Id,String$]

With this Instruction can you set the StringGadget-State. With 'Id' can
you choose the ID-Number and with String$ the State.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Get_StringGadget_State[Id]

With this Instruction can you getting the State of a StringGadget.
The result is now in 'Param$'. With 'Id' can you choose the ID-Number.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Del_StringGadget[Id]

This Instruction is like with _Del_PushButton here only for StringGadgets.
(See in addition to it _Del_PushButton.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_StringGadget_Hit

This Instruction is like with _PushButton_Hit here only for StringGadgets.
(See in addition to it _PushButton_Hit.)

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_TextGadget[Id,X,Y,Color1,Color2,Color3,Color4,MaxTexLen]

With this Instruction can you Drawing a TextGadget. This Gadget with
ID-Number 'Id' will Drawing on the Coordinaates X,Y. Color1 is the Color
for the Top & Left Border and Color2 for the Right & Bottom Border. With
Color3 can you choose the GadgetColor and Color4 for the Text in the Gadget.
With MaxTexLen can you choose the length (in Characters) of the Gadget.
You can defined Max. 30 TextGadgets. The 'Id-No.' must so have a number
from 1-30.

Info
----

An TextGadget is no Button that you can clicking. It is only for Messages.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_Set_TextGadget_Text[Id,String$]

With this Instruction can you set the State of a TextGadget. The Gadget
with ID-Number 'Id' get now the Text String$. If the Text is belonger
as the TextGadget, the Text will get automatically the length of the
TextGadget.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ScreenBar[Title$]

With this Instruction can you set a Screenbar. With 'Title$' can you choose
a Text for showing in the Screenbar.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

_WinClone[X1,Y1,X2,Y2,Title$]

With this Instruction can you drawing a Clone of an Intuition-Window in
the AMOS-Screen. This Instruction is only for showing Intuition-Windows
in the AMOS-Screen. It is so only for creating better designs. Therefore
can you also not move this Windows. :-)

With 'X1,Y1,X2,Y2' can you choose the coordinaates for the WindowClone
and with 'Title$' you can set the WinClone-Name.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@ENDNODE


@NODE Use "How to use the GadTools?"

How to use the GadTools?
------------------------

With it you can using the GadTools, you must including the GadTools
on your Mainprogramm. In addition to it can you use the 'Include'-
Instruction of AMOSPro V2.00. Go to the last Line of your Program
an type now:

Include "Device+Path/GadTools.Inc"

For Device+Path must you now insert the correct Path, whit it AMOSPro
can it found.

(Please read in addition to it also @{"Important" LINK Important})

@ENDNODE


