@NODE Guidelines "Guidelines"

Programmer-Guidelines, Look out this.
-------------------------------------

With it you get now problems, look out to any Instructions that you use.
If you will set more Instructions in one Line, please look out that you
type always an (Space " ") before you insert an ":" or the next Instruction.

For Example:
------------

_PushButton_Hit : If Param=1 Then Goto Label ...
               ^ ^
               | |

               2 x Space (" ")

This is the correct Editing. Normally will it AMOS insert, only not when
it is an Instruction of a Procedure. Then will AMOS Interpret it as an
AMOS 'Label'.

(Please read in addition to it also @{"Reduction" LINK Reduction})

@ENDNODE


@NODE Reduction "Reserved Local Variables & Banks."

Reserved Local Variables & Banks.
---------------------------------

The GadTools is an Include-File (Procedures) and not an directly AMOS-
Extension. Therefore exists in it also Variables & Banks. Please look out
that you not use the same it in your Mainprogramm. Therefore here now
an List of all Variables & Banks that the GadTools will using.:

Variables : A-I, X-Z, A$, B$, C$
AMOS-Banks: 501-531,601-631,701-731,801-831,901-931,1001-1031,1101-1131

I have not using Global Variables. Therefore can you use the same it in
your Mainprogramm, when you using it as Local Variables. The AMOS-Banks
holding all Datas to the Buttons. For Example; Bank 501 = PushButton 1,
Bank 502 = PushButton 2 and so. All these Banks allowed not using in your
Mainprogram. Otherwise get you problems. ;-)

@ENDNODE


