@NODE Important "AMOSPro-Monitor & Compiler!"

Important!
----------

Some Users have problems with the Monitor (F4) & Compiler if using the
GadTools. It is NOT a Bug of the AMOSPro-GadTools, but any Bugs of the
AMOSPro-Monitor & Compiler.

That is:

1) No Compiling possibly, if the GadTools will Including with the 'Include'
   Instruction.

2) The AMOSPro-Monitor (F4) shows no Lines, if you debugging your Program.

To 1) must I say, that the AMOSPro-Compiler will accept no Include-
      Instructions. (Any real AMOS-Bug)

Remedy
------

Before Compile your Program, remove the 'Include-Instruction' from your
Program and insert the File 'GadTools.inc' directly in your Mainprogram.
(Option 'Merge' into AMOSPro-Menu) Now will the Compiler accept your
Program.

To 2) must I say, that the AMOSPro-Monitor (F4) cannot showing Lines,
      if an AMOS-Program will loaded with 'Include' on the Mainprogram.
      It is so not in AMOSPro-Editor.

Remedy
------

How 1). Remove the 'Include-Instruction' from your Mainprogram and insert
the File 'GadTools.inc' directly in it. (Option 'Merge' into AMOSPro-Menu)
Now will the AMOSPro-Monitor again showing Lines, if you Debugging your
Program.

Please look out that you all 'Include' mentions in this Guide only using
with the AMOSPro-Interpreter. If you will Compile or Debugging (Monitor)
your Programs, observe this Info and you get no problems. Otherwise you
get problems, because AMOSPro have some Bugs.

@ENDNODE


